SASB.IF-EU-110a.2a;UN SDG.12.1;Total Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons. Greenhouse Gases are defined as those gases which contribute to the trapping of heat in the Earth's atmosphere and they include Carbon Dioxide (CO2), Methane, and Nitrous Oxide. Total GHG Emissions as defined in this field, equals the total of company Scope 1 and Scope 2 emissions. It does not include Scope 3 emissions. Definition of Scope 3 emissions remains subject to much interpretation and therefore there is significant variability in company reported data - this could cause undue variation in company Total GHG emissions figure. Emissions reported as CO2 only will NOT be captured in this field. Emissions reported as generic GHG emissions or CO2 equivalents (CO2e) will be captured in this field. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
