TCFD.Strategy.B.5;UN SDG.13.1;Percentage of the company's operations that are covered in its disclosures on emissions.  A blank in this field indicates that the scope of coverage on emissions was not disclosed. This field is part of the Environmental, Social or Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.13.1;Scope 1/Direct Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons. GHG are defined as those gases which contribute to the trapping of heat in the Earth's atmosphere and they include Carbon Dioxide (CO2), Methane, and Nitrous Oxide. Scope 1 Emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity. Examples of Direct Emissions include emissions from combustion in owned or controlled boilers, furnaces, vehicles , emissions from chemical production in owned or controlled process equipment. Emissions reported as CO2 only will NOT be captured in this field. Emissions reported as generic GHG emissions or CO2 equivalents (CO2e) will be captured in this field. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.13.1;Scope2/Indirect Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Emissions of the company in thousands of metric tons. Greenhouse Gases are defined as those gases which contribute to the trapping of heat in the Earth's atmosphere and they include Carbon Dioxide (CO2), Methane, and Nitrous Oxide. Scope 2 Emissions are those emitted that are a consequence of the activities of the reporting entity, but occur at sources owned or controlled by another entity. The principle source of Indirect Emissions is emissions from purchased electricity, steam and/or heating/cooling. These emissions physically occur at the facility where electricity/steam/heating/cooling is generated. Emissions reported as CO2 only will NOT be captured in this field. Emissions reported as generic GHG emissions or CO2 equivalents (CO2e) will be captured in this field. If disclosed as market-based and/or location-based emissions, location-based will be taken for this field. This field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.A.1;UN SDG.13.1;"Balance, measured in million metric tonnes (MT) represents carbon dioxide (CO2) allowances less carbon emissions. Negative number is a carbon ""deficit"". This field is available for the utilities sector. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.";Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.C.1;UN SDG.13.1;Number of European Allowances (EUA) (in millions) which were issued to company under European Emission Trading System (EU ETS). Each EUA represents one metric tonne (MT) of carbon dioxide (CO2) equivalent.  Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.C.1;UN SDG.13.1;Amount of carbon dioxide (CO2) measured in million metric tonnes (MT) which was emitted by company under the European Emission Trading System (EU ETS). Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.A.1;UN SDG.13.1;Direct nitrous oxide (N2O) emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons. Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity. Data includes both energy-related (from fuel combustion) and process-related emissions. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.11.6;Direct methane (CH4) emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons of carbon dioxide equivalent (CO2e). Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity, in accordance with the Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG) Scope 1 definition. Data includes both energy-related (from fuel combustion) and process-related emissions.  Where a company does not report emissions in CO2e, Bloomberg converts it to CO2e using a Global Warming Potential (GWP) of 28. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.11.6;Direct nitrous oxide (N2O) emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons of carbon dioxide equivalent (CO2e). Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity, in accordance with the Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG) Scope 1 definition. Data includes both energy-related (from fuel combustion) and process-related emissions.  Where a company does not report emissions in CO2e, Bloomberg converts it to CO2e using a Global Warming Potential (GWP) of 265. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.11.6;Direct hydrofluorocarbon (HFC) emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons of carbon dioxide equivalent (CO2e). Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity, in accordance with the Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG) Scope 1 definition. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.11.6;Direct perfluorocarbon (PFC) Emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons of carbon dioxide equivalent (CO2e). Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity, in accordance with the Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG) Scope 1 definition. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.11.6;Direct sulfur hexafluoride (SF6) emissions of the company, in thousands of metric tons of carbon dioxide equivalent (CO2e). Direct emissions are those emitted from sources that are owned or controlled by the reporting entity, in accordance with the Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG) Scope 1 definition. Where a company does not report emissions in CO2e, Bloomberg converts it to CO2e using a Global Warming Potential (GWP) of 23,500. Field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.B.1;UN SDG.13.1;Scope2/Indirect Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Emissions of the company in thousands of metric tons. GHGs are defined as those gases which contribute to the trapping of heat in the Earth's atmosphere and they include Carbon Dioxide (CO2), Methane, and Nitrous Oxide. Scope 2 Emissions are those emitted that are a consequence of the activities of the reporting entity, but occur at sources owned or controlled by another entity. The principle source of Indirect Emissions is emissions from purchased electricity, steam and/or heating/cooling. These emissions physically occur at the facility where electricity/steam/heating/cooling is generated. Emissions reported as CO2 only, will NOT be captured in this field. Emissions reported as generic GHG emissions or CO2 equivalents (CO2e) will be captured in this field. This field represents emissions reported using the market-based method, which is calculated using emissions factors from contractual instruments. For location-based or generally reported Scope 2 emissions, please refer to GHG Scope 2 (ES077, GHG_SCOPE_2). This field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
