TCFD.Metrics & Targets.A.1;UN SDG.13.1;Amount of greenhouse gas emissions offset by a company, in thousands of metric tonnes. This field includes all voluntary carbon offsets made through the purchase of carbon credits/certificates by a company to compensate for its emissions.  One carbon credit represents one ton of saved emissions through projects such as reforestation or the construction of new renewable energy installations.  This field captures the offset emissions in CO2 equivalents.;Environment
TCFD.Metrics & Targets.C.2;UN SDG.13.1;Carbon intensity calculated as metric tons of Greenhouse Gases (GHG) emitted per unit of production. The unit of production is defined and reported by the company. This includes Scope 1 (direct emissions) plus Scope 2 (purchased electricity). For cement companies this field reflects the gross direct CO2 (carbon dioxide) emissions per ton of cementitious product. For utilities this field reflects GHG emissions per MWh (Megawatt) generated or delivered as defined by the company. This field is part of the Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) group of fields.;Environment
